6400.name: Badge of Hyena
6400.description: The badge that indicates that its bearer's event collector grade is "hyena." Without this badge, one cannot prove one'S-Grade.

6401.name: Badge of Fox
6401.description: The badge that indicates that its bearer's event collector grade is "fox." Without this badge, one cannot prove one'S-Grade.

6402.name: Badge of Wolf
6402.description: The badge that indicates that its bearer's event collector grade is "wolf." Without this badge, one cannot prove one'S-Grade.

6403.name: Star Shard
6403.description: Starlight Festival Event A gift from the sky. When it is thrown, it creates a small explosion. Can be used as an ingredient to make other types of fireworks. Star Shard

6404.name: Gunpowder
6404.description: Starlight Festival Event - Black powder. An ingredient used to make larger fireworks.

6405.name: Magnesium
6405.description: Starlight Festival Event - A chemical compound that generates a powerful flash when ignited. It is needed to make large fireworks.

6406.name: Firework
6406.description: An explosive device that brilliantly lights up the sky. Firework

6407.name: Large Firework
6407.description: A large explosive device that ignites to light up the sky. Large Firework

6408.name: Formal Wear
6408.description: Formal wear appears as a wedding dress for female characters and as a tuxedo for male characters.

6409.name: 2006 Battle Tournament - CP Potion
6409.description: Restores CP by 200. CP Gauge Potion

6410.name: 2006 Battle Tournament - Quick Healing Potion
6410.description: A magical potion that quickly restores HP. However, its effects do not last. Quick Healing Potion
